<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-03T04:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-03T04:25:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/430: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">George</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-03T12:00:00+02:35">July 3, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 3—9:40
                                        a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>50. Monday night<note n="29" xml:id="d486fn29">July 1.</note>
                                    British Minister informed Emperor that Eden had proposed to
                                    Mussolini rectification Somali frontier involving cession of
                                    Ethiopian territory to Italy, to be compensated by cession to
                                    Ethiopia of British port Zeila and corridor to sea, but that
                                    Mussolini had rejected. British initiative was taken without
                                    consulting Emperor. Anticipate fresh Ethiopian appeal for moral
                                    support of the United States and shall be guided by instructions
                                    already received<note n="30" xml:id="d486fn30">See telegram No.
                                        22, December 18, 1934, 5 p.m., to the Chargé in Ethiopia,
                                            <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_769">
                                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 769</ref>.</note> in so
                                    far as possible.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>